description: From Middle English walwisch, equivalent to wallow (“tasteless, bland”) +‎ -ish.

adjectives.description: wallowish (comparative more wallowish, superlative most wallowish)

entries.meaning: (archaic) Tasteless or having an unpleasant taste; nauseous, sickly-sweet.
examples: I have eaten some, whereof the taste is somewhat sweet and wallowish.
